# Line-ending and binary-classification policy (issue #800).
#
# Default: our source and configuration normalize to LF in the index and on
# checkout. `text=auto` auto-detects binary content (files with NUL bytes, etc.)
# and leaves it alone; `eol=lf` forces LF for everything git treats as text, so
# LF is the only line ending that can be committed for normalized text -- on
# Windows checkouts included.
#
# Scope: this normalizes OUR source. Vendored / third-party / model / golden
# fixtures are deliberately preserved byte-for-byte (stable sha256) by the
# `-text` rules at the bottom -- we do not rewrite the line endings of model
# files or reference outputs we did not author.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Binary files: never line-ending-converted ------------------------------
# Images
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.webp  binary

# Fonts
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.eot   binary

# Documents / spreadsheets
*.pdf   binary
*.xls   binary
*.xlsx  binary

# Serialized protobuf instances (DB-compatible; never line-ending-converted)
*.pb       binary
*.protobin binary

# Vensim binary data/model files (.vdf/.vdfx/.vmf are undocumented binary
# formats; see docs/design/vdf.md). gitattributes matching is case-sensitive,
# so the uppercase extensions Vensim emits are listed explicitly.
*.vdf  binary
*.VDF  binary
*.vdfx binary
*.VMF  binary
*.vmf  binary

# Python sources normalize to LF (folded in from the prior #596 rule; now
# redundant under the `* text=auto eol=lf` default, kept for clarity).
*.py text eol=lf

# Linguist hints (GitHub language stats); unrelated to line endings.
src/app/scripts/* linguist-vendored
src/app/config/* linguist-vendored
src/simlin-engine/src/stdlib.gen.rs linguist-generated=true
src/simlin-engine/src/project_io.gen.rs linguist-generated=true

# --- Preserve byte-for-byte (no EOL conversion) -----------------------------
# These rules come last so they win over the `* text=auto eol=lf` default for
# any overlap. `-text` (not `binary`) so the files still produce textual diffs.
#
# Model definition files (Vensim .mdl/.MDL, Stella/XMILE .stmx/.itmx/.xmile),
# wherever they live: many are vendored or are reference fixtures whose exact
# bytes (and sha256) we keep stable, and we don't rewrite their line endings.
*.mdl   -text
*.MDL   -text
*.stmx  -text
*.itmx  -text
*.xmile -text

# The entire test/ tree is third-party / reference fixtures: vendored model
# corpora (test-models, sdeverywhere -- each with its own LICENSE/README/build
# scripts) plus golden simulation outputs (.tab/.csv/.dat/.CIN). Keep it
# pristine and byte-identical to upstream.
test/** -text

# Model + golden test fixtures that live under src/ (engine/binding tests) are
# data, not source, so they are exempt from the src/ LF normalization and kept
# byte-exact (e.g. the SIR_output.csv golden the libsimlin tests reference).
src/libsimlin/testdata/**          -text
src/pysimlin/tests/fixtures/**     -text
src/simlin-serve/tests/fixtures/** -text
